# Trivy vulnerability suppressions for SPARC
# ============================================================================
# Each suppressed CVE includes classification, justification, mitigating
# controls, and reference links. Review and re-evaluate on each major release.
#
# Classifications:
#   DISPUTED    — Upstream maintainers or NVD dispute the vulnerability
#   MITIGATED   — Real vulnerability but fully mitigated by SPARC's deployment
#   FALSE POSITIVE — Not a vulnerability; expected behavior or wrong context
# ============================================================================

# CVE-2019-1010022 — glibc stack guard page bypass
# Classification: DISPUTED (NVD, glibc maintainers)
# Description: Theoretical stack guard page bypass in glibc. Requires local
#   code execution to exploit, which already constitutes full compromise.
# Mitigation: SPARC container runs as non-root user (UID 1000) with no
#   setuid binaries. Container isolation (namespaces, seccomp) limits attack
#   surface. No known exploit exists in the wild.
# Reference: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=22850
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2019-1010022

# CVE-2011-3389 — BEAST attack on SSL 3.0 / TLS 1.0 CBC ciphers
# Classification: MITIGATED
# Description: Browser Exploit Against SSL/TLS (BEAST) enables chosen-plaintext
#   attack against CBC ciphers in SSL 3.0 and TLS 1.0.
# Mitigation: SPARC enforces TLS 1.2+ via Rails force_ssl configuration and
#   infrastructure-level TLS termination (nginx/ALB). TLS 1.0 and 1.1 are not
#   offered or accepted. CBC cipher suites in TLS 1.0 are unreachable.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2011-3389
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2011-3389

# CVE-2005-2541 — tar does not warn on setuid/setgid file extraction
# Classification: FALSE POSITIVE (expected behavior per GNU tar documentation)
# Description: GNU tar extracts files with setuid/setgid bits without warning.
#   This is documented expected behavior, not a security defect.
# Mitigation: SPARC does not extract untrusted tar archives at runtime.
#   Container builds use only official Debian package repositories with
#   signed-by GPG verification. Production container runs as non-root (UID 1000)
#   so extracted setuid bits would have no privilege escalation effect.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2005-2541
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2005-2541

# CVE-2025-24294 — resolv ReDoS vulnerability (Ruby stdlib)
# Classification: FALSE POSITIVE (container scan vs operational runtime mismatch)
# Description: ReDoS in resolv gem < 0.6.1. Trivy scans the system-level Ruby
#   stdlib gems baked into the ruby:3.4.4-slim Docker base image and finds
#   resolv 0.6.0. However, SPARC never uses this system copy at runtime.
# Why Trivy scan differs from operational runtime:
#   Trivy performs static filesystem analysis of /usr/local/lib/ruby/gems/ and
#   finds the vulnerable system-bundled resolv 0.6.0. At runtime, Bundler's
#   BUNDLE_DEPLOYMENT mode (set in Dockerfile ENV) ensures ALL gem loads come
#   from BUNDLE_PATH (/usr/local/bundle), not the system default. SPARC's
#   Gemfile pins resolv >= 0.7.0, and Gemfile.lock resolves to 0.7.1 (patched).
#   The system copy is never loaded, never executed, and unreachable via any
#   SPARC code path.
# Mitigation: Gemfile explicitly pins resolv >= 0.7.0. Verified resolv 0.7.1
#   in Gemfile.lock. BUNDLE_DEPLOYMENT=1 enforces Bundler load path isolation.
# Base image note: Tested ruby:3.4.5-slim and ruby:3.4.6-slim — resolv bumped
#   to 0.6.2 but still flagged. No Ruby 3.4.x base fully resolves this.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-24294
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2025-24294

# CVE-2025-61594 — uri vulnerability (Ruby stdlib)
# Classification: FALSE POSITIVE (container scan vs operational runtime mismatch)
# Description: Vulnerability in uri gem < 1.0.4. Trivy scans the system-level
#   Ruby stdlib and finds uri 1.0.3 baked into the ruby:3.4.4-slim base image.
#   However, SPARC never uses this system copy at runtime.
# Why Trivy scan differs from operational runtime:
#   Trivy performs static filesystem analysis and finds the vulnerable
#   system-bundled uri 1.0.3. At runtime, Bundler's BUNDLE_DEPLOYMENT mode
#   (set in Dockerfile ENV) ensures ALL gem loads come from BUNDLE_PATH
#   (/usr/local/bundle), not the system default. SPARC's Gemfile.lock resolves
#   uri to 1.1.1 (patched, latest). The system copy is never loaded, never
#   executed, and unreachable via any SPARC code path.
# Mitigation: Gemfile.lock pins uri 1.1.1 (patched). BUNDLE_DEPLOYMENT=1
#   enforces Bundler load path isolation. No Ruby 3.4.x base ships uri >= 1.0.4.
# Base image note: Tested ruby:3.4.5-slim and ruby:3.4.6-slim — uri remains
#   1.0.3 in all available Ruby 3.4.x base images. Fix expected in Ruby 3.5.x.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-61594
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2025-61594

# CVE-2025-7458 — SQLite integer overflow
# Classification: REMEDIATED (package removed from image in #342)
# Description: Integer overflow in SQLite. Removed from production image —
#   libsqlite3-0 was a transitive dependency never used by SPARC (PostgreSQL only).
# Reviewed: 2026-04-05
CVE-2025-7458

# CVE-2023-45853 — zlib MiniZip integer overflow / heap overflow
# Classification: ACCEPTED RISK (no fix available in Debian Bookworm)
# Description: Integer overflow and resultant heap-based buffer overflow in
#   zlib's minizip contrib code. No Debian Bookworm patch available.
# Mitigation: SPARC does not use minizip functionality directly. The zlib
#   library is used for HTTP compression (handled by Ruby/Rack middleware)
#   which does not exercise the minizip code path. Container runs as non-root
#   (UID 1000) limiting exploit impact.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-45853
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2023-45853

# CVE-2026-0861 — glibc vulnerability (libc-bin / libc6)
# Classification: ACCEPTED RISK (no fix available in Debian Bookworm)
# Description: Vulnerability in glibc 2.36. No Debian Bookworm patch available.
# Mitigation: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000) in isolated Docker
#   namespace with seccomp profiles. Will be resolved when base image upgrades
#   to newer Debian release with patched glibc.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-0861
# Reviewed: 2026-03-19
CVE-2026-0861

# CVE-2023-2953 — OpenLDAP null pointer dereference
# Classification: REMEDIATED (package removed from image in #342)
# Description: Null pointer dereference in libldap. Removed from production
#   image — libldap-2.5-0 was a transitive dependency of curl, never used by SPARC.
# Reviewed: 2026-04-05
CVE-2023-2953

# DS-0002 — Trivy filesystem misconfiguration: image runs as root
# Classification: FALSE POSITIVE for production
# Description: Trivy fs scan reports DS-0002 against tests/api/Dockerfile,
#   the dev/CI test-runner image used to execute the Python pytest suite
#   against a deployed SPARC instance. tests/api/Dockerfile is NOT the
#   production image — it's CI tooling that runs ephemerally in GitHub
#   Actions. The production Dockerfile (./Dockerfile, ruby:3.4.4-slim base)
#   already runs as non-root UID 1000 and is properly hardened (#342).
# Mitigation: dev/test image isolation; never deployed to production.
#   Reviewed annually as part of test-tooling audit.
# Reference: trivy-fs scan run 25409853872 against tests/api/Dockerfile
# Reviewed: 2026-05-06
DS-0002
